CC0 1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0) Public Domain Dedication

The MECP protocol specification, message format, and code table are
dedicated to the public domain under CC0 1.0.

Anyone may implement MECP without restriction. The protocol must remain
free forever. No permission is needed to build software that encodes,
decodes, transmits, or displays MECP messages.

Full legal text: https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode

This applies to:
- The protocol specification (spec/ directory)
- The code table definitions
- The message format specification
- The MECP_Developer_Brief_v2.md document
